### Step 5: Position in ring

Ring k has 6k numbers = 156 numbers for k=26.  
First number in ring 26 is 1952.  
So 2026 is the (2026-1952+1) = 75th number in ring 26 (counting from 1).

Ring k is divided into 6 sides of length k. Side length here = 26.  
75th number in ring: Which side?  
Sides: 1 to 26 (side1), 27 to 52 (side2), 53 to 78 (side3), etc.

75 is in side3 (53 to 78), position in side = 75-53+1=23rd number on side3.

Side3 is the top-left side (if starting side1 from "east" going counterclockwise).

